An Act authorizing the Plymouth County Retirement System to grant creditable service to David
Osborne.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Notwithstanding any general or special law, rule or regulation to the
2 contrary, the Plymouth county retirement system shall credit David Osborne with creditable
3 service for the service he rendered for the Town of Norwell for the period of July 1, 2008 to the
4 present, inclusive, for the purpose of determining his superannuation retirement allowance
5 pursuant to paragraph (a) of subdivision (2) of section 5 of chapter 32 of the General Laws.
6 Before the date that any retirement allowance becomes effective in the case of David Osborne,
7 he shall pay into the annuity savings fund of the retirement system in one sum or installments,
8 upon such terms and conditions as the retirement system may prescribe, an amount equal to that
9 which would have been withheld as regular deductions from his regular compensation for such
10 previous service, or most recent portion thereof, as he may elect, had he been a member of the
